A FOOTBALL coach had his eye blacked when he was punched to the ground in a touchline brawl.
Gary Wilcox, assistant manager of junior side Bo’ness United, was knocked out briefly.
Police confirmed last night they have received a complaint about the incident during a home cup clash with Musselburgh Athletic on Wednesday.
A witness claimed Gary, 50, intervened to calm the situation when a non-player from Musselburgh kicked a Bo’ness defender.But he was hit and needed to be taken away for treatment.
 

Gary posted a picture of his injuries on Facebook and wrote: “Well done mate. Hope you’re proud of yourself, you’ve upset my kids.”
 

